cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper presents a machine learning automation toolbox that automates large-scale evaluation and benchmarking of machine learning algorithms on a large number of datasets. The paper also conducts a large-scale supervised classification study to benchmark the performance of machine learning algorithms, including deep learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, since the study involves supervised classification, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since deep learning algorithms are included, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
